'''Ithorian [[Brandy/Legends|brandy]]''' was only "Ithorian" in that it was made by an [[Ithorian/Legends|Ithorian]]. It was made by [[Vanster Enan]] and sold in his [[Vanster Enan's Sop House|cantina]] on [[Cularin/Legends|Cularin]] as the house special. He made it from the fermented sap of trees found in Cularin's jungles. It was fairly tasty, and had a mild pine aftertaste. Vanster Enan sold it in large snifters for 2 credits, cheaper than any imported drink, and was willing to sell a cask of the brandy for 20 credits.<ref name="ACP">{{LivingForce|Eye of the Sun: A Cularin Presence}}</ref>

A score of such casks found their way off planet and onto the [[Darkside (space station)|Darkside]] [[Asteroid/Legends|asteroid]] base within the [[Cularin asteroid belt]].<ref name="MW">{{LivingForce|Between the Worlds: MidWorld}}</ref>

In [[31 BBY/Legends|31 BBY]], [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Alec (Jedi)|Alec]] enjoyed a couple of cups of Ithorian brandy, and then his dancing movements suddenly went sore.<ref name="cp">{{LivingForce|Clouds of Genarius: Clouded Paths}}</ref>

